The NDDO methods pioneered by Dewar and Thiel use the Dewar-Sabelli [13–15]-Klopman [16] (DSK) approximation, Eq. 1, which is equivalent to the Ohno approximation [17], for the two-electron two center integral γAB involving atoms A and B separated by a distance RAB.
